iv id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yuf1665702721962.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yuf1665702721962.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yuf1665702721962.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yuf1665702721962\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Cause macros to be processed before the rest of the keyboard input queue is\n    handled.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"yuf1665702721962__topic_d141209e1_d141210e1_d141211e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yuf1665702721962__p_d141212e1_d141213e1_d141214e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$MACRO_FIRST</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yuf1665702721962__section_mqh_vy4_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d272461e68\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yuf1665702721962__table_d16841e1_d16842e1_d16843e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">application assignment files</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yuf1665702721962__section_mh2_xy4_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d272461e115\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yuf1665702721962__p_d141221e1_d141222e1_d141223e1\">The default behavior of Uniface is to process all\n        other keys in the keyboard input queue until the queue is empty, and then to process any\n        macros. Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$MACRO_FIRST</span> to 1 causes macros to be processed before\n        the rest of the keyboard input queue is handled.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dom1695191702402.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Macro Definitions</a><p>The translation table compiler supports up to ten macros, ^M0 through ^M9, for commonly-used combinations.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534268\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534268\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$MACRO_FIRST Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 30, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Cause macros to be processed before the rest of the keyboard input queue is handled. $MACRO_FIRST = 1 | 0 Defaults Assignment file: application assignment files Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: 0 Description The default behavior of Uniface is to process all other keys in the keyboard input queue until the queue is empty, and then to process any macros. Setting $MACRO_FIRST to 1 causes macros to be processed before the rest of the keyboard input queue is handled. Related Links Macro Definitions The translation table compiler supports up to ten macros, ^M0 through ^M9, for commonly-used combinations. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}